feat: cascading-tier race + Claude-CLI proactive elaboration

Adds the "speak first, elaborate later" orchestration design:

1. Cascading-tier race for the immediate answer (model="auto"):
   - T1 (Groq/Cerebras/SambaNova, 2s deadline) — typical winner
   - T2 (Claude-CLI/DeepSeek/Gemini, 5s deadline) — fallback
   - T3 (OpenRouter-large/Kimi/Groq-slow, no deadline) — last resort
   - Tier providers are env-driven via TIER{1,2,3}_PROVIDERS and
     TIER{1,2}_DEADLINE_S.

2. Parallel Claude-CLI elaboration track (inspiring-cat worker):
   - submit-once-poll-twice pattern: same task feeds the T2 race AND a
     longer-deadline elaboration poll (180s).
   - When Claude returns and its answer is materially different from the
     spoken answer (length ratio + difflib similarity heuristic), a
     "Sir, may I elaborate?" banner appears and is spoken via Web Speech.
   - User Yes -> Claude's answer is rendered + spoken.
   - User Not now -> banner clears.

3. Browser-native TTS (window.speechSynthesis):
   - tts.onTokenStream feeds streamed deltas; flushes on sentence
     boundaries.
   - tts.cancel fires when the user starts a new turn.

Backend (new):
- src/openjarvis/server/tier_cascade.py — race orchestrator
- src/openjarvis/server/claude_cli_client.py — inspiring-cat task client
  (POST /tasks {type:"claude_pro", payload:{prompt}}, GET /tasks/{id})
- src/openjarvis/server/elaboration_store.py — in-memory state + SSE pubsub
- src/openjarvis/server/elaboration_worker.py — poll + diff + push
- src/openjarvis/server/elaboration_routes.py — SSE stream + accept/dismiss

Backend (modified):
- src/openjarvis/server/routes.py — _handle_stream wires cascade + spawns
  elaboration; writes spoken_answer back when stream finishes
- src/openjarvis/server/app.py — register elaboration_router

Frontend (new):
- frontend/src/lib/tts.ts — Web Speech API wrapper
- frontend/src/lib/elaborations.ts — long-lived SSE subscriber
- frontend/src/components/ElaborationBanner.tsx — Yes/Not now UI

Frontend (modified):
- InputArea.tsx — feed deltas to TTS, cancel on new turn
- store.ts — proposedElaborations state + actions
- App.tsx — mount elaboration SSE on boot
- ChatArea.tsx — render <ElaborationBanner /> above input
- CommandPalette.tsx — surface "auto" cascade as a first-class model

Auth: claude_cli_client.py reads INSPIRING_CAT_WEBHOOK_SECRET first,
falls back to CLAUDE_SESSION_TOKEN, then no auth. Inspiring-cat /tasks
currently accepts unauthenticated POSTs; this is forward-compat for when
they're locked down.

Defer to follow-up: Postgres persistence for elaborations, server-side
TTS, embedding-based diff heuristic, security gate.
